713726f-a.title: Manhattan: 54th Street (West) - 7th Avenue
713726f-a.text:
Vest 54th Street, north side, west from No. 145 (right) a point east of Seventh Ave., and across same to Broadway (extreme left) showing in the foreground several former garages converted into night clubs. These enterprises were an outgrowth of Prohibition. The apartment house shown at the N.E. corner replaced the Grace Dutch Reformed Church that
stood there.
October 22, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

The Maih Garage bears No. 140-138. On the left, at the N.E. corner of Sixth Ave., appears a portion of the 36-story aparthment house, The Warick. This set consists of a
